an be some confusion around vaping, even with it becoming more mainstream. There are a few points to this question to pick apart to help you know exactly what it is you are buying when you purchase an e-liquid or when you’re thinking about vaping.&nbsp;<br></span></p></div></div></div><div class="pf-54ef692f pf-r pf-r-eh sc-iGPElx fnjRwB" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c pf-c-xs--12 pf-c-sm--12 pf-c-md--12 pf-c-lg--12" style="padding: 15px;"><div class="pf-3aa6f896 sc-etwtAo hYUmfZ" data-pf-type="Column"><h3 mode="view" class="pf-b64111fb sc-rBLzX gJheEP" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-867b5526 sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">Do vapes contain tobacco?<br></span></h3><p class="pf-7670f076 sc-likbZx dYIPIx" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-2999eb3d sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">None. No tobacco whatsoever will be found in your e-liquid. However, you can buy <a href="https://vapeandjuice.co.uk/collections/tobacco-flavours" target="_self">tobacco flavoured e-liquid</a>. This is ideal for people who have recently quit smoking and want to enjoy the authentic tobacco taste. Otherwise, you will not find tobacco or tobacco flavouring in your e-liquid. As we are all too aware, burning tobacco causes cancer risk, along with many other diseases.<br></span></p><h3 mode="view" class="pf-ea9b7a13 sc-rBLzX gJheEP" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-ea69016d sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">Do vapes contain nicotine?&nbsp;<br></span></h3><p class="pf-2909ad6d sc-likbZx dYIPIx" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-a3759518 sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">Yes and no. You can select your own nicotine content depending on your need. In the UK the highest nicotine level is 18mg. You can also get 11mg, 6mg, 3mg and 0mg. 0mg contains zero nicotine. You might use zero-nicotine e-liquids if you were gradually weaning yourself off of it. Or if you are into chasing clouds and doing tricks then you might use a zero.<br></span></p><h3 mode="view" class="pf-c07df721 sc-rBLzX gJheEP" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-2b1bbb62 sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">What are the health risks of vaping?<br></span></h3><p class="pf-5f30b033 sc-likbZx dYIPIx" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-abde9539 sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">We know that smoking is the leading cause of preventable death in the UK. This is why many people are moving onto replace it with vaping. Vaping allows people to keep up the habit of smoking, enjoy the throat hit, have a dose of nicotine and taste some great flavours. Vaping is relatively new so there are not many long term studies on it. We have seen some fake news and sensationalist journalism on <a href="https://vapeandjuice.co.uk/blogs/main-blog/vaping-lung-collapse" target="_self">vaping causing a lung to collapse</a>, but this is unfounded. In fact, Public Health England has declared vaping as 95% safer than smoking.</span></p><h3 mode="view" class="pf-8350984a sc-rBLzX gJheEP" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-ab636597 sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">Can you quit vaping?<br></span></h3><p class="pf-e1e81716 sc-likbZx dYIPIx" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-8f90b644 sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">If you decide to quit vaping then you would need to gradually reduce your nicotine intake. You do this by going from a high 18mg right down to a 6mg, 3mg and finally a 0mg. When you are on 0mg your nicotine dependency will be beaten and you will find that you don’t need to vape.&nbsp;</span></p><h3 mode="view" class="pf-7e8687df sc-rBLzX gJheEP" data-pf-type="Heading"><span class="pf-1c5e743a sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">Where do I buy vapes without nicotine or tobacco?<br></span></h3><p class="pf-33d70793 sc-likbZx dYIPIx" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span class="pf-d08db509 sc-iybRtq cdiHjD" data-pf-type="Text">You can buy your nicotine and tobacco-free vapes at Vape and Juice. We have shops all over the UK, we also have a website whe